**Note**: You must not change the existing SQL query or add a new one. Your solution must be built based on the available query result only.

**Database Table (std_info):**
| std_id | std_name | std_major |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| 111 | duha | CIS |
| 222 | Ahmad | BIT |
| 333 | leen | CIS |
| 444 | kareem | CS |

**PHP Code:**
```php
$db = mysql_connect("localhost", "root", "12345678");
mysql_select_db("students3", $db);
$q = "select * from std_info";
$result = mysql_query($q, $db);
mysql_close($db);
print("<table border='1'>");

// Fill the missing code that should be here

